👉 Exceptions in JAVA

An Exception is an event that occurs when a program is executed disrupting the normal flow of instructions.
There are mainly two types of exceptions in Java :

1. Checked Exception -> Compile the exceptions (Handled by compiler)
2. Unchecked Exception -> Runtime exceptions

Commonly occuring Exceptions :

following are few commonly occuring exceptions in JAVA :
1. Null Pointers Exception
2. Arithmetic Exception
3. Array Index Out of Bound Exception
4. Illegal Argument Exception
5. Number format Exception

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

👉 In Java, a try-catch (exception handling) block is used to handle runtime errors (exceptions) so that your program doesn’t crash abruptly.

Basic Syntax 

try {
    // Code that may cause an exception
} catch (ExceptionType e) {
    // Code to handle the exception
}


Sample Code : 

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            int a = 10;
            int b = 0;
            int result = a / b;   // This will cause an exception
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ArithmeticException e) {
            System.out.println("Cannot divide by zero!");
        }
    }
}

